[music]

154
00:10:27.417 --> 00:10:32.000
[music]

155
00:10:32.083 --> 00:10:33.333
[Sadewo] What's wrong?

156
00:10:33.417 --> 00:10:35.125
[Bumi] My mom told me to go home.

157
00:10:35.208 --> 00:10:36.500
[Bumi] Sounded important.

158
00:10:36.833 --> 00:10:43.041
[upbeat music]

159
00:10:43.125 --> 00:10:44.375
[Bumi] Bro, here.

160
00:10:46.042 --> 00:10:47.125
Cheers, Bro.

161
00:10:47.208 --> 00:10:48.500
Enjoy, okay?

162
00:10:50.250 --> 00:10:51.333
Hey.

163
00:10:52.917 --> 00:10:54.917
Thank you.

164
00:10:55.000 --> 00:10:56.000
Cheers.

165
00:10:57.625 --> 00:10:58.820
[mumbling]

166
00:10:58.901 --> 00:11:04.108
[upbeat music]

167
00:11:04.205 --> 00:11:07.835
[car slow driving]

168
00:11:19.549 --> 00:11:21.257
[Paris] Ma'am, whose photo is this?

169
00:11:21.958 --> 00:11:23.638
[footsteps approaching]

170
00:11:23.722 --> 00:11:26.055
This is my son, Bumi.

171
00:11:26.139 --> 00:11:27.847
The one who picked you up.

172
00:11:28.760 --> 00:11:31.375
Oh. Sorry, I thought...

173
00:11:31.472 --> 00:11:34.597
Bumi is a driver who works here.

174
00:11:34.682 --> 00:11:36.849
Bumi is on holiday.

175
00:11:36.930 --> 00:11:40.014
[Rahmi] He is currently studying
in his final semester in Jakarta.

176
00:11:43.389 --> 00:11:45.264
[Rahmi] That photo...

177
00:11:45.347 --> 00:11:48.555
was from his last
birthday with his father.

178
00:11:50.347 --> 00:11:53.097
Have a drink, Paris. Go on.

179
00:11:53.180 --> 00:11:54.389
Thank you.

180
00:11:54.472 --> 00:11:57.878
[car arrive and stop]

181
00:11:57.972 --> 00:12:00.815
[footsteps approaching]

182
00:12:01.514 --> 00:12:03.139
[Bumi] Mom.

183
00:12:03.222 --> 00:12:06.389
Sorry, Ma'am. I completely forgot
that your stuff...

184
00:12:06.472 --> 00:12:08.198
I accidentally brought
your stuff with me, Miss.

185
00:12:08.222 --> 00:12:10.347
I'll bring it to you.

186
00:12:10.430 --> 00:12:11.680
Sorry, Ma'am.

187
00:12:11.764 --> 00:12:14.305
I told you to call me Paris.

188
00:12:14.389 --> 00:12:15.972
Not Miss or Ma'am.

189
00:12:17.264 --> 00:12:18.889
Yes.

190
00:12:18.972 --> 00:12:20.097
Paris.

191
00:12:21.389 --> 00:12:24.097
Sorry, Mom. It's not that I'm rude...

192
00:12:24.180 --> 00:12:26.222
Paris. Sorry, Paris.

193
00:12:27.555 --> 00:12:30.097
Let me take Paris home.

194
00:12:33.083 --> 00:12:34.263
- Excuse me, Ma'am.
- Yes.

195
00:12:34.347 --> 00:12:35.639
- [Rahmi] Thank you.
- Please.

196
00:12:37.014 --> 00:12:38.014
Yes.

197
00:12:38.555 --> 00:12:40.433
[car driving]

198
00:12:40.514 --> 00:12:42.680
Out of all my stuff...

199
00:12:42.764 --> 00:12:45.347
why did my pink suitcase
get left behind in your car?

200
00:12:47.889 --> 00:12:49.305
You did it on purpose, didn't you?

201
00:12:53.574 --> 00:12:54.682
[awkward laughing]

202
00:12:57.722 --> 00:13:01.097
Mrs. Rahmi, the owner of this rental car...

203
00:13:02.847 --> 00:13:04.597
is your mother?

204
00:13:04.680 --> 00:13:05.930
So what?

205
00:13:08.097 --> 00:13:09.764
Do you want to apologize...

206
00:13:09.847 --> 00:13:12.514
because you told
me to carry your things?

207
00:13:12.597 --> 00:13:14.222
Why should I apologize?

208
00:13:15.555 --> 00:13:17.680
I've paid for the car rental.

209
00:13:18.722 --> 00:13:21.222
Why do I have to carry my own things?

210
00:13:27.347 --> 00:13:28.764
I'm hungry.

211
00:13:28.847 --> 00:13:30.972
Restaurants are about to close.

212
00:13:31.055 --> 00:13:34.722
We can look for takeaway meal or...

213
00:13:34.805 --> 00:13:35.889
do delivery order.

214
00:13:36.972 --> 00:13:38.514
Anything you want to eat specifically?

215
00:13:42.305 --> 00:13:44.555
- Seafood, meat?
- Anything.

216
00:13:45.847 --> 00:13:47.987
[disappointed sigh]

217
00:13:48.055 --> 00:13:53.089
[motorbike passing]

218
00:13:56.083 --> 00:13:58.364
[Bumi] Check again
if any of your items have gone missing.

219
00:13:59.639 --> 00:14:02.014
There's no way
an undergraduate student steals.

220
00:14:02.097 --> 00:14:04.014
[Bumi] Well...

221
00:14:04.097 --> 00:14:06.180
What did my mother tell you about me?

222
00:14:06.264 --> 00:14:07.389
[Paris] Hmm?

223
00:14:10.847 --> 00:14:12.430
Okay then. Gotta go.

224
00:14:12.514 --> 00:14:14.874
What time do you want to be
picked up tomorrow by Mr. Kadek?

225
00:14:14.930 --> 00:14:17.139
No, I don't want Mr. Kadek.

226
00:14:17.222 --> 00:14:19.097
I want to be with you.

227
00:14:19.180 --> 00:14:21.055
I'm not a driver.

228
00:14:21.139 --> 00:14:23.472
I only replaced Mr. Kadek
whose child was sick.

229
00:14:24.555 --> 00:14:26.305
[Paris] Hey, wait.

230
00:14:26.389 --> 00:14:29.764
I told you I couldn't eat alone.

231
00:14:29.847 --> 00:14:32.430
You bought me food,
so you should accompany me to eat.

232
00:14:36.430 --> 00:14:37.597
I forgot about that.

233
00:14:38.764 --> 00:14:40.055
That's right. Come on.

234
00:14:44.503 --> 00:14:52.503
[phone ringing]

235
00:14:56.847 --> 00:14:58.764
Your cell phone rang just now.

236
00:14:58.847 --> 00:15:00.264
Oh.

237
00:15:01.399 --> 00:15:02.562
[mumbling]

238
00:15:02.929 --> 00:15:04.038
My mother.

239
00:15:05.055 --> 00:15:07.430
I'll call her back later.

240
00:15:09.313 --> 00:15:15.421
[water pouring]

241
00:15:19.050 --> 00:15:20.198
[Sighing]

242
00:15:21.389 --> 00:15:22.805
Cheers.

243
00:15:22.889 --> 00:15:24.722
For life.

244
00:15:24.805 --> 00:15:25.972
Cheers.

245
00:15:30.219 --> 00:15:31.320
[sipping]

246
00:15:37.764 --> 00:15:39.055
You're lucky.

247
00:15:41.847 --> 00:15:43.847
To have Bali as your home.

248
00:15:44.889 --> 00:15:47.472
It feels like
enjoying life in heaven.

249
00:15:49.625 --> 00:15:53.208
The place where you live
is also a beautiful city, right?

250
00:15:57.222 --> 00:15:59.097
By the way, why is your name Paris?

251
00:15:59.180 --> 00:16:00.805
Since you were born in Bali.

252
00:16:03.188 --> 00:16:04.554
[mumbling]

253
00:16:05.555 --> 00:16:08.055
My mother gave me that name.

254
00:16:08.139 --> 00:16:09.305
Oh.

255
00:16:11.180 --> 00:16:12.597
Back then...

256
00:16:12.680 --> 00:16:16.597
my mother had a dream
of raising her child in Paris.

257
00:16:18.014 --> 00:16:21.389
That's why my mother gave me
the name Paris.

258
00:16:21.472 --> 00:16:25.097
Because to her,
I was one of her dreams that came true.

259
00:16:28.222 --> 00:16:31.139
But unfortunately,
not all of her dreams came true.

260
00:16:32.972 --> 00:16:35.514
That's why I return to Bali.

261
00:16:39.347 --> 00:16:41.847
And you coming back here...

262
00:16:41.930 --> 00:16:45.722
is that what you want?

263
00:16:55.055 --> 00:16:56.805
I...

264
00:16:56.889 --> 00:16:59.597
always learn...

265
00:16:59.680 --> 00:17:02.847
that expectations will end
in disappointments.

266
00:17:07.514 --> 00:17:09.055
So, as much as possible...

267
00:17:11.833 --> 00:17:14.958
I believe in what is best for me.

268
00:17:16.555 --> 00:17:19.305
So, if you ask whether...

269
00:17:19.389 --> 00:17:24.097
this is exactly what I imagined
before I came here...

270
00:17:25.139 --> 00:17:26.389
the answer is...

271
00:17:28.722 --> 00:17:30.180
Well...

272
00:17:31.597 --> 00:17:35.014
This is more than I imagined.

273
00:17:35.097 --> 00:17:36.722
Because you met a driver like me?

274
00:17:37.889 --> 00:17:39.680
[laughing]

275
00:17:39.764 --> 00:17:40.889
Because...

276
00:17:40.972 --> 00:17:43.680
I was picked up by a guy...

277
00:17:43.764 --> 00:17:46.597
who I thought was a driver...

278
00:17:46.680 --> 00:17:50.097
and what people think,
when he brought my stuff...

279
00:17:50.180 --> 00:17:51.472
that he was my boyfriend.

280
00:17:51.555 --> 00:17:53.430
But...

281
00:17:53.514 --> 00:17:56.055
it turns out the plot twist is...

282
00:17:56.139 --> 00:17:57.389
he's not a driver.

283
00:17:57.781 --> 00:17:59.054
[giggling]

284
00:18:00.889 --> 00:18:04.347
I don't know what God's intention was
by sending him to pick me up.

285
00:18:08.805 --> 00:18:10.555
Sorry.

286
00:18:10.639 --> 00:18:12.847
Don't get too excited.

287
00:18:12.930 --> 00:18:15.389
It wasn't God who sent me.

288
00:18:15.472 --> 00:18:16.521
It was my mother.

289
00:18:16.605 --> 00:18:20.917
[laughing]

290
00:18:21.000 --> 00:18:24.513
[laughing]

291
00:18:24.597 --> 00:18:26.305
Geez.

292
00:18:26.389 --> 00:18:30.639
It's been a while
since I laughed this freely.

293
00:18:30.922 --> 00:18:33.951
[laughing]

294
00:18:39.055 --> 00:18:41.055
When did you feel the happiest?

295
00:18:43.092 --> 00:18:50.544
[soft music]

296
00:18:52.430 --> 00:18:53.680
[Bumi] Psst!

297
00:18:53.764 --> 00:18:55.014
[Bumi] Mr. Kadek!

298
00:18:58.722 --> 00:18:59.972
Yes, what?

299
00:19:04.097 --> 00:19:05.264
Mr. Kadek.

300
00:19:05.347 --> 00:19:06.764
Tomorrow...

301
00:19:06.847 --> 00:19:09.055
you should just look after your child.

302
00:19:09.139 --> 00:19:10.472
Let me take the guest around.

303
00:19:10.555 --> 00:19:13.514
- Are you sure?
- Uh-huh!

304
00:19:13.597 --> 00:19:14.805
- Got it?
- Okay.

305
00:19:15.972 --> 00:19:17.389
Your child is number one.

306
00:19:17.472 --> 00:19:18.472
Okay.

307
00:19:18.555 --> 00:19:21.097
Let me handle the guest.

308
00:19:21.180 --> 00:19:22.514
I bet the guest is beautiful.

309
00:19:22.597 --> 00:19:23.972
Nonsense.

310
00:19:24.055 --> 00:19:25.472
It's not like that.

311
00:19:25.555 --> 00:19:26.889
I feel sorry for you.

312
00:19:26.972 --> 00:19:28.865
- I don't want you to leave your sick child.
- Is that so?

313
00:19:28.889 --> 00:19:30.222
Uh-huh! Okay?

314
00:19:30.305 --> 00:19:31.930
- Okay, thanks then.
- Okay.

315
00:19:32.014 --> 00:19:33.680
- But don't tell anyone.
- Yes, for sure.

316
00:19:33.764 --> 00:19:34.847
- Promise?
- For sure.

317
00:19:34.930 --> 00:19:37.124
- Thumb? Thumb.
- Okay.

318
00:19:37.208 --> 00:19:41.667
[soft music]

319
00:19:41.764 --> 00:19:46.794
[footsteps walking down stairs]

320
00:19:46.889 --> 00:19:49.435
[spraying parfume]

321
00:19:52.415 --> 00:19:54.641
[footsteps walking down stairs]

322
00:19:56.597 --> 00:19:58.514
Hi, good morning.

323
00:19:58.597 --> 00:19:59.889
Why are you here?

324
00:19:59.972 --> 00:20:01.639
Mr. Kadek's not picking me up?

325
00:20:01.722 --> 00:20:03.305
His child is still sick.

326
00:20:03.764 --> 00:20:11.764
[upbeat music]

327
00:20:14.722 --> 00:20:18.180
This is one of Mr. Mario
Blanco's paintings.

328
00:20:18.264 --> 00:20:19.639
It's about a coconut.

329
00:20:19.722 --> 00:20:23.665
So, Mr. Mario also got a MURI achievement
for a painting with the most beautiful frame.

330
00:20:23.764 --> 00:20:30.141
[upbeat music]

331
00:20:30.222 --> 00:20:32.347
Miss, let me take you to the next place.

332
00:20:32.430 --> 00:20:33.555
[Paris] Come on.

333
00:20:33.639 --> 00:20:37.160
[upbeat music]

334
00:20:37.222 --> 00:20:39.980
[camera shutter]

335
00:20:40.055 --> 00:20:47.514
[upbeat music]

336
00:20:47.597 --> 00:20:49.604
Hold her. Be romantic.

337
00:20:49.708 --> 00:20:56.708
[upbeat music]

338
00:20:56.792 --> 00:21:03.792
[upbeat music]

339
00:21:03.875 --> 00:21:10.875
[upbeat music]

340
00:21:10.958 --> 00:21:17.958
[upbeat music]

341
00:21:18.042 --> 00:21:25.042
[upbeat music]

342
00:21:25.125 --> 00:21:32.125
[upbeat music]

343
00:21:32.208 --> 00:21:40.208
[upbeat music]

344
00:21:40.542 --> 00:21:44.042
[groaning]

345
00:21:44.376 --> 00:21:45.628
[Bumi] Sorry.

346
00:21:52.264 --> 00:22:00.264
[uplifting music]

347
00:22:02.472 --> 00:22:04.639
See?

348
00:22:04.722 --> 00:22:06.930
How annoying!

349
00:22:07.376 --> 00:22:08.883
[grunting]

350
00:22:09.555 --> 00:22:12.055
Come on. Tidy it up.

351
00:22:12.139 --> 00:22:15.889
Don't ever give up.
We must remain enthusiastic as a youngster.

352
00:22:15.972 --> 00:22:17.389
Yes?

353
00:22:17.472 --> 00:22:19.180
Don't give up easily.

354
00:22:19.264 --> 00:22:20.514
Excuse me.

355
00:22:21.138 --> 00:22:22.958
- Hello?
- Bro.

356
00:22:23.042 --> 00:22:25.417
- Where are you?
- [Bumi] <i>Sir Bro!</i>

357
00:22:25.514 --> 00:22:29.305
Sir Bro! What's up, Sir Bro?

358
00:22:29.389 --> 00:22:30.597
What's going on?

359
00:22:30.680 --> 00:22:32.068
Yes, it's me.

360
00:22:32.441 --> 00:22:33.608
Can you come here?

361
00:22:34.036 --> 00:22:35.417
[Sadewo] <i>I'm in my usual place.</i>

362
00:22:35.514 --> 00:22:37.389
With whom, Sir Bro?

363
00:22:37.472 --> 00:22:38.847
I'll be waiting for you, okay?

364
00:22:40.472 --> 00:22:41.639
Okay.

365
00:22:44.805 --> 00:22:46.433
See? You toppled it yourself.

366
00:22:46.514 --> 00:22:48.349
[laughing]

367
00:22:48.430 --> 00:22:51.014
A friend asks me to accompany him.

368
00:22:51.097 --> 00:22:54.271
But thanks for your stupid face.

369
00:22:57.264 --> 00:22:58.722
Thank you for today.

370
00:22:58.805 --> 00:23:01.389
But you can't let this be this messy.
Let's tidy it up first.

371
00:23:01.472 --> 00:23:02.597
First, cheers.

372
00:23:03.001 --> 00:23:04.172
[clinking glasses]

373
00:23:04.264 --> 00:23:12.264
[soft music]

374
00:23:14.639 --> 00:23:16.097
[Paris's mom] <i>Good evening.</i>

375
00:23:16.180 --> 00:23:17.222
Good evening.

376
00:23:19.764 --> 00:23:20.847
I miss you, Mom.

377
00:23:21.667 --> 00:23:23.375
I miss you too, my darling.

378
00:23:23.472 --> 00:23:25.764
So, have you found
what you were looking for?

379
00:23:27.583 --> 00:23:29.042
[Paris's mom] <i>Honey...</i>

380
00:23:29.139 --> 00:23:32.889
<i>I had told you
before you left for Bali.</i>

381
00:23:32.972 --> 00:23:34.680
Are you sure you want to do this?

382
00:23:36.805 --> 00:23:38.764
I'm sure.

383
00:23:40.347 --> 00:23:43.430
I'll never regret my decision
to come to Bali.

384
00:23:43.857 --> 00:23:45.249
[Paris] <i>And I'm also sure...</i>

385
00:23:45.341 --> 00:23:47.424
that I can find
what I'm looking for.

386
00:23:51.014 --> 00:23:54.214
When people are trying to relax, there
could only be two problems in their lives.

387
00:23:55.389 --> 00:23:57.097
First...

388
00:23:57.180 --> 00:23:58.805
money problem.

389
00:23:58.889 --> 00:23:59.972
And the second?

390
00:24:00.055 --> 00:24:01.514
Calm down.

391
00:24:02.639 --> 00:24:04.180
Woman problem.

392
00:24:04.264 --> 00:24:05.347
I'm sure about that.

393
00:24:08.805 --> 00:24:10.139
Hey, Bro.

394
00:24:10.222 --> 00:24:11.722
- Bro.
- [Bumi] Huh?

395
00:24:11.805 --> 00:24:13.680
[Sadewo] Listen to me first.

396
00:24:13.764 --> 00:24:14.930
You're crazy, aren't you?

397
00:24:15.014 --> 00:24:16.639
Can't you see how stressed I am?

398
00:24:17.847 --> 00:24:20.264
That woman really ruined my life.

399
00:24:21.764 --> 00:24:23.264
Destroyed my pride.

400
00:24:24.472 --> 00:24:28.013
Not only my pride as a husband,
but my pride as a man!

401
00:24:28.847 --> 00:24:30.389
I'm done.

402
00:24:30.472 --> 00:24:33.014
- How come?
- I don't know.

403
00:24:33.097 --> 00:24:34.930
Oh, dear...

404
00:24:35.014 --> 00:24:37.972
You shouldn't accept that, Sir Bro.
In my opinion, you should fight.

405
00:24:38.055 --> 00:24:41.430
- You can't just do nothing.
- Do you think I didn't do all that?

406
00:24:41.514 --> 00:24:42.847
[Sadewo] Ouch!

407
00:24:42.930 --> 00:24:46.075
- Honey, I'm sorry.
- [Sadewo's wife] You want to fight?

408
00:24:49.014 --> 00:24:53.472
Have you forgotten
that I know all your secrets?

409
00:24:53.555 --> 00:24:55.764
Or do you want to go to jail?

410
00:24:55.848 --> 00:24:57.181
Is that so?

411
00:24:58.722 --> 00:25:02.180
Looking at your appearance,
about money...

412
00:25:02.264 --> 00:25:04.389
I'm sure
you have no problem with that.

413
00:25:04.472 --> 00:25:05.847
Last order.

414
00:25:05.930 --> 00:25:07.722
- [Sadewo] Oh, right.
- Let me.

415
00:25:07.805 --> 00:25:09.139
- You have money?
- I have.

416
00:25:09.222 --> 00:25:10.222
Calm down.

417
00:25:16.055 --> 00:25:18.889
But looking at your appearance...

418
00:25:18.972 --> 00:25:20.847
- [Bumi] Thank you.
- [waitress] Thank You.

419
00:25:20.930 --> 00:25:26.014
Which woman wants to be with a man
who has money but acts like a homeless?

420
00:25:26.097 --> 00:25:28.055
Hey, you don't think I'm cool?

421
00:25:28.139 --> 00:25:29.305
You're cool.

422
00:25:29.389 --> 00:25:30.472
So, what's the problem?

423
00:25:32.014 --> 00:25:33.180
You're just not neat.

424
00:25:34.222 --> 00:25:35.347
I can't be neat.

425
00:25:35.430 --> 00:25:37.180
That's the problem!

426
00:25:37.264 --> 00:25:41.347
Sometimes people think,
"Okay, my appearance is okay enough."

427
00:25:41.430 --> 00:25:43.055
Well, that can't be allowed, Sir Bro.

428
00:25:43.139 --> 00:25:45.055
As men, we can't be content easily.

429
00:25:45.139 --> 00:25:47.389
[Bumi] One day, we should look different.

430
00:25:47.472 --> 00:25:49.232
[Bumi] It's okay to be
neat once in a while.

431
00:25:49.305 --> 00:25:52.161
Boom! Push your chest forward like this.

432
00:25:53.472 --> 00:25:55.139
I'm sure women will love it!

433
00:25:55.222 --> 00:25:56.222
Shh!

434
00:25:56.305 --> 00:25:57.406
Come with me tomorrow, Sir Bro.

435
00:25:57.430 --> 00:25:59.430
- To do what?
- I'll make you presentable.

436
00:25:59.514 --> 00:26:00.972
Come on, I've paid.

437
00:26:01.055 --> 00:26:02.055
Let's go.

438
00:26:02.139 --> 00:26:09.624
[uplifting music]

439
00:26:09.708 --> 00:26:17.034
[uplifting music]

440
00:26:17.118 --> 00:26:18.454
[Bumi] Handsome.

441
00:26:18.555 --> 00:26:25.349
[uplifting music]

442
00:26:25.430 --> 00:26:27.281
[Bumi] We're going to the barber,
not a burger place.

443
00:26:27.305 --> 00:26:28.985
- We'll eat later.
- Where else will we go?

444
00:26:29.055 --> 00:26:30.847
All good!

445
00:26:30.930 --> 00:26:32.139
This?

446
00:26:32.222 --> 00:26:34.055
Okay, Sir Bro.

447
00:26:34.139 --> 00:26:35.247
Relax.

448
00:26:35.328 --> 00:26:37.205
[footsteps walking down stairs]

449
00:26:37.722 --> 00:26:39.183
[Door opening]

450
00:26:39.264 --> 00:26:41.847
Good morning, Miss. I'm Kadek.

451
00:26:41.930 --> 00:26:43.896
Wait, where's Bumi?

452
00:26:45.458 --> 00:26:48.624
Please. Do you want to sit in the front
or in the back?

453
00:26:50.042 --> 00:26:58.042
[uplifting music]

454
00:27:00.749 --> 00:27:08.749
[uplifting music]

455
00:27:10.668 --> 00:27:11.683
[grunting]

456
00:27:12.972 --> 00:27:14.172
[Bumi] Sir Bro, are you ready?

457
00:27:14.222 --> 00:27:15.305
[Sadewo] Ready!

458
00:27:17.805 --> 00:27:19.097
[Peter] Mr. Sadewo.

459
00:27:22.055 --> 00:27:23.139
Yes?

460
00:27:25.430 --> 00:27:27.222
Do you still remember me?

461
00:27:27.305 --> 00:27:29.416
- Peter.
- Yes, I remember. Peter.

462
00:27:29.500 --> 00:27:31.393
[Peter] We haven't seen each other for a long
time. I still remember the last time we met...

463
00:27:31.417 --> 00:27:33.126
you were drunk with Siska.

464
00:27:34.472 --> 00:27:35.514
Oh, yes.

465
00:27:36.514 --> 00:27:38.347
Pleased to meet you again.

466
00:27:38.430 --> 00:27:39.764
- I'll go in.
- Okay.

467
00:27:43.514 --> 00:27:44.764
[Bumi] All good, Sir Bro?

468
00:27:44.847 --> 00:27:52.847
[electro house music]

469
00:27:57.347 --> 00:27:58.472
Thank you.

470
00:27:58.555 --> 00:28:01.930
[electro house music]

471
00:28:02.014 --> 00:28:03.347
- [Bumi] Yup.
- [Sadewo] Yes!

472
00:28:04.764 --> 00:28:08.597
To life, women, and freedom.

473
00:28:08.680 --> 00:28:09.805
Salute.

474
00:28:09.889 --> 00:28:15.433
[electro house music]

475
00:28:15.514 --> 00:28:16.680
[Sadewo] Thank you, Bro.

476
00:28:17.889 --> 00:28:20.264
You've been my lifesaver.

477
00:28:20.347 --> 00:28:22.430
What are you talking about?
No way.

478
00:28:24.305 --> 00:28:26.055
Thank you so much.

479
00:28:26.139 --> 00:28:27.416
Cheers.

480
00:28:27.500 --> 00:28:32.375
[electro house music]

481
00:28:32.472 --> 00:28:33.639
I want to ask you a question.

482
00:28:35.180 --> 00:28:36.389
You're handsome.

483
00:28:37.972 --> 00:28:39.264
You'll finish college soon.

484
00:28:39.347 --> 00:28:42.474
[electro house music]

485
00:28:42.555 --> 00:28:43.639
Do you have a girlfriend?

486
00:28:43.722 --> 00:28:48.099
[electro house music]

487
00:28:48.180 --> 00:28:49.764
No, Sir Bro.

488
00:28:49.847 --> 00:28:51.722
You're crazy.

489
00:28:51.805 --> 00:28:53.847
I already know this kind of trickery.

490
00:28:55.625 --> 00:28:58.641
A playboy like you would say that.

491
00:29:00.639 --> 00:29:01.805
I'm serious, Sir Bro.

492
00:29:01.889 --> 00:29:04.529
If you don't have a girlfriend,
you won't be able to be my teacher.

493
00:29:06.347 --> 00:29:09.384
I'm serious, Sir Bro.
Why won't you believe me?

494
00:29:12.347 --> 00:29:13.993
Bring your girl here.

495
00:29:14.597 --> 00:29:15.764
Introduce her to me.

496
00:29:17.180 --> 00:29:18.764
Don't act as if you're low profile.

497
00:29:20.972 --> 00:29:24.407
Drinking is the only way
for me to calm down.

498
00:29:24.491 --> 00:29:26.474
Why is that, Sir Bro?

499
00:29:26.555 --> 00:29:29.847
I've always taken the wrong path.

500
00:29:29.930 --> 00:29:32.180
[Sadewo] I left a good girl.

501
00:29:34.511 --> 00:29:37.136
And I got a girl
which makes my life like hell instead.

502
00:29:38.122 --> 00:29:40.622
Wait, what do you mean?

503
00:29:40.706 --> 00:29:42.298
How can it be like that?

504
00:29:42.764 --> 00:29:44.430
I'm like most other men.

505
00:29:44.514 --> 00:29:46.722
I never think with this,
but with this.

506
00:29:46.805 --> 00:29:47.805
This!

507
00:29:47.850 --> 00:29:49.472
[lauhing]

508
00:29:49.555 --> 00:29:51.222
Sir Bro, that's normal.

509
00:29:51.305 --> 00:29:53.930
All men think with this first,
and with this afterward.

510
00:29:54.014 --> 00:29:55.055
Okay.

511
00:29:56.097 --> 00:29:58.097
That's normal.

512
00:29:58.180 --> 00:29:59.889
But you know, right?

513
00:29:59.972 --> 00:30:01.555
My life is done.

514
00:30:02.889 --> 00:30:04.472
You know...

515
00:30:04.555 --> 00:30:07.055
your wife is a successful woman.

516
00:30:07.139 --> 00:30:08.597
Successful?

517
00:30:08.680 --> 00:30:10.264
Hey, listen to me.

518
00:30:11.514 --> 00:30:14.847
If she's successful,
I wouldn't be done like this.

519
00:30:16.042 --> 00:30:18.333
What I should keep...

520
00:30:18.430 --> 00:30:19.829
I let go.

521
00:30:19.917 --> 00:30:21.337
Here's the thing, Sir Bro.

522
00:30:21.792 --> 00:30:24.251
There is a proverb.

523
00:30:24.500 --> 00:30:28.708
A successful man...

524
00:30:28.792 --> 00:30:33.013
is a man who can get more income...

525
00:30:33.097 --> 00:30:35.946
than what his wife spends.

526
00:30:36.042 --> 00:30:38.042
And a successful woman...

527
00:30:38.125 --> 00:30:42.000
is a woman who can get a man like you.

528
00:30:42.097 --> 00:30:43.930
- Is that so?
- Yes!

529
00:30:44.528 --> 00:30:45.996
[giggling]

530
00:30:46.555 --> 00:30:51.555
The proof is that now you can still support
your family. You can still live well.

531
00:30:53.597 --> 00:30:55.097
- Sir Bro.
- Yes.

532
00:30:58.347 --> 00:31:00.055
There's a story, Sir Bro.

533
00:31:01.722 --> 00:31:03.389
There is an area...

534
00:31:03.472 --> 00:31:06.139
which has a very deep well.

535
00:31:07.639 --> 00:31:11.639
[Bumi] And in this well,
scary jinns await.

536
00:31:13.097 --> 00:31:14.305
And over there...

537
00:31:15.685 --> 00:31:17.935
there are only two living creatures.

538
00:31:18.019 --> 00:31:19.561
A married couple.

539
00:31:22.063 --> 00:31:24.805
When her husband wants to be free...

540
00:31:24.889 --> 00:31:28.110
he brings his wife
towards the well...

541
00:31:28.208 --> 00:31:30.749
and he throws her into the well.

542
00:31:32.225 --> 00:31:34.433
- Imagine...
- And then?

543
00:31:34.517 --> 00:31:37.101
how bad that man wants to be free.

544
00:31:39.343 --> 00:31:41.135
But what happens afterward, Sir Bro?

545
00:31:41.219 --> 00:31:44.415
Five minutes later,
all the jinns run away.

546
00:31:44.500 --> 00:31:46.125
Scared of the wife.

547
00:31:46.209 --> 00:31:47.530
Wait.

548
00:31:47.614 --> 00:31:48.780
Hey.

549
00:31:50.305 --> 00:31:51.972
I don't understand your story.

550
00:31:52.055 --> 00:31:57.016
[funny music]

551
00:31:57.097 --> 00:31:59.680
That means
the alcohol level is really high.

552
00:31:59.764 --> 00:32:01.972
Let's have another toast then.

553
00:32:02.055 --> 00:32:05.139
[Sadewo] To women,
life, and freedom! Cheers!

554
00:32:05.222 --> 00:32:06.264
Free!

555
00:32:07.061 --> 00:32:09.217
[laughing]

556
00:32:09.805 --> 00:32:13.055
Gosh, that's really bad.

557
00:32:13.139 --> 00:32:16.180
[Paris] Is there really such a cruel wife?

558
00:32:16.264 --> 00:32:18.493
Well, that's what he said.

559
00:32:21.097 --> 00:32:23.204
What kind of wife
do you think you will be?

560
00:32:23.972 --> 00:32:25.722
It depends.

561
00:32:26.805 --> 00:32:27.972
Depends on her husband.

562
00:32:30.180 --> 00:32:31.472
Good point.

563
00:32:33.722 --> 00:32:34.889
What about you?

564
00:32:37.125 --> 00:32:39.083
What kind of woman are you looking for?

565
00:32:40.014 --> 00:32:42.597
A woman...

566
00:32:42.680 --> 00:32:45.889
that if her husband dies,
she will never remarry.

567
00:32:49.889 --> 00:32:51.014
What about you?

568
00:32:56.014 --> 00:32:58.847
A husband who will never leave
his family.

569
00:33:11.217 --> 00:33:13.764
[joy shouting]

570
00:33:15.264 --> 00:33:16.514
It's melting!

571
00:33:16.597 --> 00:33:20.558
[upbeat music]

572
00:33:20.639 --> 00:33:22.389
You like it?

573
00:33:22.472 --> 00:33:24.014
- Proud?
- Yes.

574
00:33:24.764 --> 00:33:26.347
[laughing]

575
00:33:26.430 --> 00:33:27.472
Come on.

576
00:33:30.722 --> 00:33:31.805
[Sadewo] Sis.

577
00:33:35.847 --> 00:33:36.930
[Sadewo] Sis.

578
00:33:39.889 --> 00:33:41.139
Where are you going?

579
00:33:43.097 --> 00:33:45.264
Don't leave. This is our house.

580
00:33:45.347 --> 00:33:47.347
- Where are you going, Sis?
- Let me go.

581
00:33:47.430 --> 00:33:48.514
I know.

582
00:33:50.014 --> 00:33:51.294
And you're still going to leave?

583
00:33:52.305 --> 00:33:53.639
Who said I'm leaving?

584
00:33:53.722 --> 00:33:54.722
That?

585
00:33:54.805 --> 00:33:55.805
Here.

586
00:33:55.889 --> 00:33:56.930
Take it.

587
00:33:58.514 --> 00:34:00.055
Wait, you can't do this.

588
00:34:00.139 --> 00:34:02.389
You can't kick me out. This is my house.

589
00:34:02.472 --> 00:34:03.972
What are you saying?

590
00:34:07.597 --> 00:34:08.764
You...

591
00:34:08.847 --> 00:34:11.014
You are no longer useful here.

592
00:34:11.097 --> 00:34:12.347
You'd better leave.

593
00:34:13.097 --> 00:34:20.264
[melodramatic music]

594
00:34:20.347 --> 00:34:21.347
Okay.

595
00:34:23.597 --> 00:34:25.555
Let me take a shower first.

596
00:34:25.639 --> 00:34:26.930
After that, I will leave.

597
00:34:27.014 --> 00:34:35.014
[melodramatic music]

598
00:34:36.208 --> 00:34:37.833
Go away quickly!

599
00:34:37.915 --> 00:34:45.332
[melodramatic music]

600
00:34:45.417 --> 00:34:52.833
[melodramatic music]

601
00:34:52.923 --> 00:35:00.340
[melodramatic music]

602
00:35:00.417 --> 00:35:04.208
[melodramatic music]

603
00:35:04.273 --> 00:35:10.398
[vehicle passing]

604
00:35:20.722 --> 00:35:22.389
I...

605
00:35:24.639 --> 00:35:26.514
I like beaches.

606
00:35:27.555 --> 00:35:29.889
I like rice fields.

607
00:35:29.972 --> 00:35:31.305
And I like mountains.

608
00:35:35.805 --> 00:35:38.514
Because for me,
to enjoy the beauty of nature...

609
00:35:38.597 --> 00:35:39.972
there is a balance of soul.

610
00:35:41.180 --> 00:35:43.055
[Paris] Balance?

611
00:35:43.139 --> 00:35:44.264
[Bumi] Yes.

612
00:36:05.657 --> 00:36:12.657
[soft music]

613
00:36:12.750 --> 00:36:19.750
[soft music]

614
00:36:19.833 --> 00:36:27.833
[soft music]

615
00:36:27.993 --> 00:36:29.196
[startled]

616
00:36:31.597 --> 00:36:32.597
Oh, dear.

617
00:36:32.680 --> 00:36:33.805
[Bumi] Be careful.

618
00:36:33.889 --> 00:36:37.599
[Bumi] Relax.

619
00:36:37.680 --> 00:36:38.972
It hurts, doesn't it?

620
00:36:39.055 --> 00:36:43.683
[soft music]

621
00:36:43.764 --> 00:36:45.555
Just hold on to me, no need to be shy.

622
00:36:45.639 --> 00:36:52.558
[soft music]

623
00:36:52.639 --> 00:36:54.264
Are you still alone?

624
00:36:54.347 --> 00:36:55.514
What do you mean?

625
00:36:56.680 --> 00:36:57.764
Single?

626
00:36:59.680 --> 00:37:01.597
Why are you asking?

627
00:37:03.222 --> 00:37:04.472
[Paris] Back then...

628
00:37:05.764 --> 00:37:10.492
I saw and felt my mother's pain
when my father left her...

629
00:37:11.139 --> 00:37:12.639
for another woman.

630
00:37:13.722 --> 00:37:14.805
Sorry.

631
00:37:14.889 --> 00:37:16.461
I'm sorry for you.

632
00:37:16.937 --> 00:37:19.722
[Bumi] Is that why you asked
if I'm still single?

633
00:37:19.805 --> 00:37:21.889
[Bumi] Is that so? Because you're afraid...

634
00:37:21.972 --> 00:37:23.892
that if someone sees
us together like this...

635
00:37:23.930 --> 00:37:25.264
you will hurt each other?

636
00:37:26.792 --> 00:37:28.125
[laughing]

637
00:37:28.222 --> 00:37:34.891
[soft music]

638
00:37:35.083 --> 00:37:37.666
And if I say I'm still single...

639
00:37:37.748 --> 00:37:38.998
what are you going to do?

640
00:37:42.555 --> 00:37:44.347
Because people won't ask that...

641
00:37:44.430 --> 00:37:47.014
if they don't have the motivation
to fill that void.

642
00:37:47.097 --> 00:37:54.849
[soft music]

643
00:37:54.930 --> 00:37:56.367
No need to be nervous.

644
00:37:57.972 --> 00:38:02.305
[uplifting music]

645
00:38:02.389 --> 00:38:03.805
She's just proud.

646
00:38:03.875 --> 00:38:05.833
[uplifting music]

647
00:38:05.930 --> 00:38:07.305
[Sadewo] Good afternoon, Gek.

648
00:38:07.389 --> 00:38:08.514
[Gek] Afternoon.

649
00:38:08.597 --> 00:38:10.805
[Sadewo] I want to meet Bumi.

650
00:38:10.889 --> 00:38:11.972
[Sadewo] Is this his house?

651
00:38:12.055 --> 00:38:13.624
Yes.

652
00:38:13.708 --> 00:38:15.499
- Good afternoon, Ma'am.
- [Rahmi] Yes.

653
00:38:16.764 --> 00:38:18.389
I want to meet Bumi.

654
00:38:18.472 --> 00:38:19.889
And who are you?

655
00:38:19.972 --> 00:38:21.180
I'm his friend.

656
00:38:22.889 --> 00:38:23.930
His friend?

657
00:38:24.014 --> 00:38:25.097
Yes.

658
00:38:27.472 --> 00:38:30.347
[Sadewo] I tried to call him,
but he didn't pick up.

659
00:38:30.430 --> 00:38:32.514
Maybe the signal was bad.

660
00:38:32.597 --> 00:38:35.014
Bumi is taking a guest around.

661
00:38:35.097 --> 00:38:37.597
How do you know Bumi?

662
00:38:37.680 --> 00:38:38.805
Oh.

663
00:38:40.889 --> 00:38:44.472
Bumi has helped me several times.

664
00:38:45.930 --> 00:38:47.764
Do you want to rent a car?

665
00:38:47.847 --> 00:38:49.930
Let my staff drive you around.

666
00:38:50.014 --> 00:38:52.222
You'll need to wait a long time for Bumi.

667
00:38:54.165 --> 00:38:55.749
[Rahmi] Come on, Sir.

668
00:38:55.833 --> 00:38:58.583
I'm worried that Bumi
will come back at night.

669
00:39:00.117 --> 00:39:01.641
It's okay, Ma'am.

670
00:39:02.101 --> 00:39:03.430
I'll wait for him.

671
00:39:03.514 --> 00:39:05.764
- Is that so?
- [Sadewo] If I may.

672
00:39:05.847 --> 00:39:08.014
- Have a drink then.
- Yes, thank you.

673
00:39:14.542 --> 00:39:16.500
May I have a look at that, Ma'am?

674
00:39:16.597 --> 00:39:17.722
[Rahmi] Yes.

675
00:39:17.805 --> 00:39:19.139
Please.

676
00:39:26.790 --> 00:39:29.749
[Sadewo] Oh, this is
Bumi when he was little.

677
00:39:29.833 --> 00:39:30.875
Yes.

678
00:39:32.458 --> 00:39:34.875
Bumi often talks about you.

679
00:39:34.972 --> 00:39:37.055
But he never talked about his father.

680
00:39:39.083 --> 00:39:40.791
[Sadewo] Where is his father now?

681
00:39:44.264 --> 00:39:45.805
His father...

682
00:39:48.514 --> 00:39:52.014
We never know what happened to him.

683
00:39:57.397 --> 00:40:00.564
[Rahmi] That's why Bumi...

684
00:40:00.648 --> 00:40:02.648
hates his birthday.

685
00:40:03.750 --> 00:40:06.958
I never knew what happened to my husband.

686
00:40:07.042 --> 00:40:08.667
[Rahmi] Only God knows...

687
00:40:10.972 --> 00:40:13.264
what happened to...

688
00:40:15.889 --> 00:40:17.472
Bumi's father.

689
00:40:19.656 --> 00:40:21.615
I'm sorry to hear that.

690
00:40:22.597 --> 00:40:23.722
[Rahmi] Thank you.

691
00:40:23.805 --> 00:40:30.961
[sad music]

692
00:40:31.042 --> 00:40:38.846
[sad music]

693
00:40:38.930 --> 00:40:40.055
[Rahmi] Hey.

694
00:40:40.139 --> 00:40:41.389
[Rahmi] Who is he?

695
00:40:41.472 --> 00:40:43.597
- My friend.
- [Rahmi] Who is he?

696
00:40:55.180 --> 00:40:56.608
[Bumi] Sir Bro.

697
00:40:56.680 --> 00:40:57.881
[grunting]

698
00:40:59.042 --> 00:41:00.333
Who is he?

699
00:41:02.732 --> 00:41:03.791
Sir Bro...

700
00:41:03.875 --> 00:41:05.443
[grunting]

701
00:41:06.764 --> 00:41:07.930
Sir.

702
00:41:09.305 --> 00:41:10.597
Sir.

703
00:41:10.680 --> 00:41:12.471
[Sadewo] Gosh, Ma'am. Do you need to sit?

704
00:41:12.555 --> 00:41:14.058
[laughing]

705
00:41:14.139 --> 00:41:15.430
Sorry, Ma'am.

706
00:41:15.667 --> 00:41:17.166
Sir Bro, did you get kicked out?

707
00:41:17.250 --> 00:41:18.417
You don't know that.

708
00:41:19.606 --> 00:41:22.106
Sorry, Ma'am. I fell asleep.

709
00:41:22.190 --> 00:41:23.732
Can I borrow Bumi for a while?

710
00:41:25.076 --> 00:41:26.742
I'll bring him back home. Promise.

711
00:41:28.222 --> 00:41:29.472
It won't be long, Mom.

712
00:41:29.555 --> 00:41:30.764
It'll be quick.

713
00:41:34.597 --> 00:41:36.055
I need to change my shirt.

714
00:41:36.139 --> 00:41:37.583
In my room.

715
00:41:37.667 --> 00:41:38.834
Over there.

716
00:41:41.097 --> 00:41:42.347
Borrow?

717
00:41:42.430 --> 00:41:43.805
Just a moment.

718
00:41:43.889 --> 00:41:45.805
Who is that, anyway?

719
00:41:45.889 --> 00:41:46.930
Who?

720
00:41:47.014 --> 00:41:52.890
[electro house music]

721
00:41:52.992 --> 00:41:54.250
[clinking glasses]

722
00:41:57.667 --> 00:41:59.375
[Sadewo] This is a photo of my child.

723
00:42:00.430 --> 00:42:01.555
[Sadewo] Beautiful, huh?

724
00:42:02.667 --> 00:42:04.667
- Beautiful.
- Beautiful?

725
00:42:04.958 --> 00:42:06.250
Very beautiful.

726
00:42:08.264 --> 00:42:11.805
When she was five years old,
her mother took her abroad.

727
00:42:13.935 --> 00:42:17.726
And since then, I haven't known how...

728
00:42:18.972 --> 00:42:21.055
How to contact her.

729
00:42:21.136 --> 00:42:26.599
[electro house music]

730
00:42:26.680 --> 00:42:28.055
[Sadewo] Well...

731
00:42:29.792 --> 00:42:32.333
[Sadewo] It was fifteen years ago.

732
00:42:32.430 --> 00:42:33.889
I never move.

733
00:42:35.139 --> 00:42:37.874
I never change my address.

734
00:42:37.958 --> 00:42:39.166
Know why?

735
00:42:41.680 --> 00:42:45.891
My hope is that one day,
my child will come and look for me.

736
00:42:48.180 --> 00:42:52.097
And that the woman I love
will someday look for me too.

737
00:42:52.180 --> 00:42:58.808
[electro house music]

738
00:42:58.889 --> 00:43:00.180
It will happen, Sir Bro.

739
00:43:00.264 --> 00:43:03.222
[electro house music]

740
00:43:03.305 --> 00:43:04.773
[Sadewo] I know...

741
00:43:05.847 --> 00:43:07.847
fifteen years ago
I was too selfish.

742
00:43:07.930 --> 00:43:10.472
[Sadewo] Pursuing my ambitions.

743
00:43:10.555 --> 00:43:12.722
My wife only asked for one thing
at that time.

744
00:43:12.805 --> 00:43:14.555
"Do you have time?"

745
00:43:14.639 --> 00:43:16.889
"Just pay a little attention to us."

746
00:43:16.972 --> 00:43:19.558
[electro house music]

747
00:43:19.639 --> 00:43:21.555
I didn't do it.

748
00:43:21.639 --> 00:43:24.055
I didn't pay attention,
let alone have time.

749
00:43:24.139 --> 00:43:27.224
[electro house music]

750
00:43:27.305 --> 00:43:28.665
[Sadewo] Until finally she said...

751
00:43:29.680 --> 00:43:31.916
"What are you going to choose?"

752
00:43:32.000 --> 00:43:33.750
Ambition is indeed a choice.

753
00:43:34.930 --> 00:43:35.930
[Sadewo] Yes.

754
00:43:37.222 --> 00:43:38.222
[Sadewo] Enough already.

755
00:43:39.680 --> 00:43:41.014
Here.

756
00:43:41.097 --> 00:43:42.972
Enough of my sad story.

757
00:43:43.055 --> 00:43:44.889
Your turn, tell me a story.

758
00:43:44.972 --> 00:43:46.930
I've been telling you my sad story.

759
00:43:48.167 --> 00:43:49.760
Listen.

760
00:43:49.844 --> 00:43:51.583
You've made me happy.

761
00:43:51.667 --> 00:43:54.083
Now it's my turn to make you happy.

762
00:43:54.180 --> 00:43:56.014
Invite your girl here.

763
00:43:56.097 --> 00:43:57.972
Introduce her to me.

764
00:43:58.055 --> 00:43:59.264
I'll treat you.

765
00:44:00.597 --> 00:44:01.889
Okay?

766
00:44:01.972 --> 00:44:03.055
Thank you, Sir Bro.

767
00:44:03.722 --> 00:44:04.770
[clinking glasses]

768
00:44:07.764 --> 00:44:08.764
[Paris] Why are you here?

769
00:44:09.764 --> 00:44:11.972
I miss your stupid face.

770
00:44:12.055 --> 00:44:13.055
Seriously?

771
00:44:13.139 --> 00:44:14.865
I have somewhere to go.
Do you want to accompany me?

772
00:44:14.889 --> 00:44:15.972
Why me?

773
00:44:17.514 --> 00:44:20.389
Because my friend asked me
to bring my girlfriend.

774
00:44:20.472 --> 00:44:22.972
But the only girl I'm close to is you.

775
00:44:23.055 --> 00:44:25.097
So, well...

776
00:44:25.180 --> 00:44:26.758
be my pretend girlfriend.

777
00:44:27.597 --> 00:44:30.139
Please. Come on. Okay?

778
00:44:30.222 --> 00:44:31.722
[Bumi] No need to be proud. Come on.

779
00:44:31.805 --> 00:44:33.805
Come on. That's okay. Come on.

780
00:44:33.889 --> 00:44:35.808
[uplifting music]

781
00:44:35.889 --> 00:44:37.341
[laughing]

782
00:44:37.430 --> 00:44:42.609
[uplifting music]

783
00:44:42.680 --> 00:44:49.221
[uplifting music]

784
00:44:49.305 --> 00:44:51.614
[Paris] Why you give that
thumb? Do I look good?

785
00:44:54.597 --> 00:44:56.192
[holding laughter]

786
00:44:57.542 --> 00:45:00.096
[vehicles passing]

787
00:45:04.639 --> 00:45:06.180
Look at the sky tonight.

788
00:45:07.750 --> 00:45:09.083
[Bumi] Do you know...

789
00:45:09.180 --> 00:45:12.211
why there's only a few stars tonight?

790
00:45:15.014 --> 00:45:16.180
Don't know?

791
00:45:18.180 --> 00:45:20.891
That's because
you are beautiful tonight.

792
00:45:22.417 --> 00:45:24.626
So, all the stars are in your eyes.

793
00:45:24.875 --> 00:45:27.812
[laughing]

794
00:45:29.782 --> 00:45:36.782
[club music]

795
00:45:36.875 --> 00:45:43.875
[club music]

796
00:45:43.958 --> 00:45:50.958
[club music]

797
00:45:51.042 --> 00:45:55.388
[club music]

798
00:45:55.472 --> 00:45:57.805
[Bumi] Sir Bro!

799
00:45:57.889 --> 00:45:59.097
[Sadewo] Crazy.

800
00:45:59.180 --> 00:46:01.666
- Who are you with?
- A girl.

801
00:46:01.750 --> 00:46:03.883
- Please wait.
- [Bumi] Okay, Sir Bro.

802
00:46:05.805 --> 00:46:07.180
Sir Bro.

803
00:46:09.847 --> 00:46:11.347
- Done?
- Done.

804
00:46:14.430 --> 00:46:16.889
Later. My friend was there.

805
00:46:16.972 --> 00:46:22.651
[club music]

806
00:46:22.750 --> 00:46:29.305
[club music]

807
00:46:29.389 --> 00:46:31.264
- [Sadewo] Hey.
- Sir Bro.

808
00:46:31.347 --> 00:46:32.472
Have you been here long?

809
00:46:32.555 --> 00:46:33.722
- No.
- Want to drink?

810
00:46:33.805 --> 00:46:35.389
I already got one.

811
00:46:35.472 --> 00:46:36.805
- I've ordered.
- Okay.

812
00:46:36.889 --> 00:46:39.472
That's okay.
Sir Bro, let me introduce her to you.

813
00:46:39.555 --> 00:46:42.347
This is Sir Bro.

814
00:46:42.430 --> 00:46:43.514
Sadewo.

815
00:46:45.055 --> 00:46:46.389
Bumi never took you here before?

816
00:46:46.472 --> 00:46:47.722
Is that so?

817
00:46:49.430 --> 00:46:50.472
Yes.

818
00:46:50.555 --> 00:46:53.680
What's wrong?
What did you say your name was?

819
00:46:53.764 --> 00:46:54.889
What?

820
00:46:54.958 --> 00:47:01.958
[club music]

821
00:47:02.042 --> 00:47:09.042
[club music]

822
00:47:09.125 --> 00:47:16.023
[club music]

823
00:47:17.984 --> 00:47:18.984
Paris?

824
00:47:21.472 --> 00:47:22.555
[Sadewo] Paris.

825
00:47:23.680 --> 00:47:26.683
[tense music]

826
00:47:26.764 --> 00:47:29.933
[crying]

827
00:47:30.014 --> 00:47:31.889
Are you Paris?

828
00:47:31.972 --> 00:47:39.972
[tense music]

829
00:47:41.722 --> 00:47:42.889
Paris.

830
00:47:42.972 --> 00:47:50.972
[slow music]

831
00:47:53.639 --> 00:47:54.948
[Paris's mom] Let's blow this up, come on.

832
00:47:54.972 --> 00:47:59.683
[sad music]

833
00:47:59.764 --> 00:48:01.014
[Sadewo] Paris!

834
00:48:01.097 --> 00:48:09.097
[slow music]

835
00:48:14.930 --> 00:48:16.139
Dad.

836
00:48:18.169 --> 00:48:22.555
Mom always taught me that with love,
there's always forgiveness.

837
00:48:25.305 --> 00:48:27.389
Mom has forgiven you.

838
00:48:27.472 --> 00:48:30.514
Even though you may not deserve it.

839
00:48:30.597 --> 00:48:38.389
[slow music]

840
00:48:38.472 --> 00:48:40.514
My coming here...

841
00:48:40.597 --> 00:48:42.097
is because I'm an adult.

842
00:48:43.597 --> 00:48:45.430
And because of my own volition.

843
00:48:45.514 --> 00:48:50.014
[slow music]

844
00:48:50.097 --> 00:48:53.597
Because I deserve answers.

845
00:48:53.680 --> 00:48:57.597
Why someone who was supposed to love
and protect us...

846
00:48:57.680 --> 00:48:59.805
left us instead?

847
00:49:03.708 --> 00:49:05.333
I have the right, Dad.

848
00:49:07.347 --> 00:49:10.244
I have the right to have a life...

849
00:49:10.328 --> 00:49:14.597
and grow up with a father's love.

850
00:49:14.680 --> 00:49:17.264
[Paris] But why were my rights taken away?

851
00:49:17.526 --> 00:49:19.026
[Paris] We're the same, Dad.

852
00:49:21.430 --> 00:49:23.972
We both live in regret.

853
00:49:25.504 --> 00:49:27.462
[Paris] My regret is...

854
00:49:27.546 --> 00:49:30.249
why when I first rode a bicycle...

855
00:49:30.333 --> 00:49:32.958
when I first went to school...

856
00:49:33.046 --> 00:49:37.095
the first time
I liked a guy...

857
00:49:37.180 --> 00:49:39.347
At those times I had no father...

858
00:49:39.430 --> 00:49:43.597
to look after me, to protect me.

859
00:49:43.680 --> 00:49:46.430
Or even to scold me when I'm wrong.

860
00:49:46.514 --> 00:49:49.222
You were not there!
You were never around!

861
00:49:49.305 --> 00:49:53.555
[slow music]

862
00:49:53.639 --> 00:49:54.805
Dad...

863
00:49:54.889 --> 00:49:58.472
[slow music]

864
00:49:58.555 --> 00:49:59.930
Maybe you're right.

865
00:50:02.014 --> 00:50:03.597
My coming here...

866
00:50:05.014 --> 00:50:07.264
Maybe it's because
God has forgiven you.

867
00:50:08.632 --> 00:50:10.264
Because I'm your daughter.

868
00:50:10.347 --> 00:50:15.555
[slow music]

869
00:50:15.639 --> 00:50:18.930
But I don't have any power at all
to forgive you.

870
00:50:20.972 --> 00:50:23.222
[Paris] I can only love you...

871
00:50:24.430 --> 00:50:26.264
and get the answer to this question.

872
00:50:30.055 --> 00:50:33.097
After all this time
we've been apart...

873
00:50:36.639 --> 00:50:38.430
do you still love me?

874
00:50:38.514 --> 00:50:40.898
Ssh... Don't say that, kid.

875
00:50:42.875 --> 00:50:45.042
Listen, kid.

876
00:50:46.972 --> 00:50:48.875
I still love you.

877
00:50:50.375 --> 00:50:51.889
I still love you.

878
00:50:51.972 --> 00:50:59.972
[slow music]

879
00:51:05.160 --> 00:51:06.495
[grunting]

880
00:51:09.504 --> 00:51:11.493
[Rahmi] Bumi. Let's eat.

881
00:51:11.574 --> 00:51:14.667
Okay, mom. Wait a minute.

882
00:51:15.530 --> 00:51:22.958
[melodramatic music]

883
00:51:23.042 --> 00:51:30.458
[melodramatic music]

884
00:51:30.542 --> 00:51:33.500
[melodramatic music]

885
00:51:33.597 --> 00:51:34.597
Dad.

886
00:51:34.667 --> 00:51:42.083
[melodramatic music]

887
00:51:42.167 --> 00:51:49.583
[melodramatic music]

888
00:51:49.667 --> 00:51:57.083
[melodramatic music]

889
00:51:57.167 --> 00:52:04.234
[melodramatic music]

890
00:52:25.500 --> 00:52:26.667
[Bumi] Sir Bro.

891
00:52:27.792 --> 00:52:28.917
How are you?

892
00:52:32.750 --> 00:52:34.584
You planned everything, didn't you?

893
00:52:35.919 --> 00:52:37.585
How did you know
that Paris is my child?

894
00:52:42.514 --> 00:52:43.722
Well...

895
00:52:43.805 --> 00:52:46.097
That was when I realized that...

896
00:52:46.180 --> 00:52:48.472
Paris came here
to look for his father.

897
00:52:49.625 --> 00:52:51.708
And I just found out
that it turns out...

898
00:52:51.792 --> 00:52:53.709
that you're her father.

899
00:52:54.602 --> 00:53:02.602
[phone ringing]

900
00:53:02.750 --> 00:53:10.750
[phone ringing]

901
00:53:10.875 --> 00:53:14.833
So, I was looking for the right time
to bring you and Paris together.

902
00:53:18.089 --> 00:53:19.839
How far is your relationship?

903
00:53:20.764 --> 00:53:23.090
Well, I haven't known
her for long, Sir Bro.

904
00:53:23.174 --> 00:53:24.632
- But...
- But what?

905
00:53:26.076 --> 00:53:27.242
But what?

906
00:53:29.000 --> 00:53:30.443
[Sadewo] But you haven't known each other
for long?

907
00:53:30.467 --> 00:53:31.842
Good, then.

908
00:53:31.995 --> 00:53:34.276
That means it's easy for you
to stay away from each other.

909
00:53:37.812 --> 00:53:39.412
Why should we stay away from each other?

910
00:53:40.055 --> 00:53:41.180
You're asking me?

911
00:53:41.264 --> 00:53:42.389
Asking me why?

912
00:53:43.514 --> 00:53:45.805
All of our fun moments together...

913
00:53:45.889 --> 00:53:49.305
That's not what I expect
from my future child's partner.

914
00:53:49.389 --> 00:53:51.055
I'm a man.

915
00:53:51.139 --> 00:53:54.416
And every time I look in the mirror,
it's as if I'm talking to myself.

916
00:53:54.500 --> 00:53:56.083
I don't want...

917
00:53:56.156 --> 00:53:58.156
my child's partner
will be like me.

918
00:54:01.430 --> 00:54:02.430
Sorry.

919
00:54:03.708 --> 00:54:07.139
I'm not you,
if that's what you mean.

920
00:54:08.389 --> 00:54:12.459
What if it was the universe
that united me with Paris?

921
00:54:13.143 --> 00:54:14.768
Enough.

922
00:54:15.141 --> 00:54:16.558
I don't need your excuse.

923
00:54:17.347 --> 00:54:19.889
The most important thing for me now
is to make Paris happy...

924
00:54:19.972 --> 00:54:22.097
after 17 years of my life
full of regrets.

925
00:54:24.222 --> 00:54:25.430
Stay away from Paris.

926
00:54:26.972 --> 00:54:28.097
Okay?

927
00:54:30.639 --> 00:54:31.889
You pay for my coffee.

928
00:54:33.014 --> 00:54:34.180
[Sadewo] My cell phone.

929
00:54:34.256 --> 00:54:41.673
[melodramatic music]

930
00:54:41.750 --> 00:54:49.167
[melodramatic music]

931
00:54:49.250 --> 00:54:56.667
[melodramatic music]

932
00:54:56.750 --> 00:55:04.167
[melodramatic music]

933
00:55:04.250 --> 00:55:09.708
[melodramatic music]

934
00:55:09.805 --> 00:55:17.805
[motorcycle ride]

935
00:55:18.458 --> 00:55:25.875
[melodramatic music]

936
00:55:25.958 --> 00:55:33.375
[melodramatic music]

937
00:55:33.458 --> 00:55:37.958
[melodramatic music]

938
00:55:38.029 --> 00:55:39.531
- [Surfer] Excuse me, please.
- Alright.

939
00:55:39.555 --> 00:55:40.974
- [Bumi] Thank you.
- You are welsome.

940
00:55:40.998 --> 00:55:48.415
[melodramatic music]

941
00:55:48.500 --> 00:55:55.917
[melodramatic music]

942
00:55:56.000 --> 00:56:04.000
[melodramatic music]

943
00:56:11.498 --> 00:56:12.641
[door knocking]

944
00:56:12.833 --> 00:56:14.000
[Paris] Excuse me.

945
00:56:16.388 --> 00:56:17.389
[door knocking]

946
00:56:17.472 --> 00:56:18.472
[Rahmi] Yes.

947
00:56:18.542 --> 00:56:20.042
[footsteps approaching]

948
00:56:20.475 --> 00:56:22.482
[door creaking]

949
00:56:24.167 --> 00:56:25.375
[Rahmi] Paris?

950
00:56:27.917 --> 00:56:29.500
[Rahmi] How strange.

951
00:56:30.472 --> 00:56:34.883
Is there something urgent
that makes you look for Bumi?

952
00:56:34.967 --> 00:56:38.972
Bumi doesn't make another mistake,
like when he took your suitcase, right?

953
00:56:39.055 --> 00:56:41.416
No. Absolutely not.

954
00:56:41.500 --> 00:56:44.167
Bumi helped me...

955
00:56:44.264 --> 00:56:46.889
find someone
who had been apart from me.

956
00:56:55.180 --> 00:56:57.847
This is a photo of me
when I was little.

957
00:56:57.930 --> 00:56:59.805
[Paris] This is my mother, and...

958
00:56:59.889 --> 00:57:04.083
my father who left us for 17 years.

959
00:57:04.167 --> 00:57:07.583
[Paris] Thanks to Bumi,
I was able to find my father faster.

960
00:57:07.680 --> 00:57:10.972
[Paris] Before, I only had this photo
to get to know my father.

961
00:57:11.042 --> 00:57:18.042
[tense music]

962
00:57:18.125 --> 00:57:25.125
[tense music]

963
00:57:25.208 --> 00:57:28.708
[tense music]

964
00:57:28.805 --> 00:57:32.363
[car passing]

965
00:57:32.805 --> 00:57:34.308
[footsteps approaching]

966
00:57:34.389 --> 00:57:35.389
Dad.

967
00:57:35.472 --> 00:57:36.472
Hey.

968
00:57:36.930 --> 00:57:38.472
[grunting]

969
00:57:38.667 --> 00:57:39.792
[Sadewo] Sit down, Kid.

970
00:57:44.708 --> 00:57:47.541
I couldn't wait for us to meet.

971
00:57:47.623 --> 00:57:48.789
I miss you.

972
00:57:49.859 --> 00:57:50.943
Have you eaten?

973
00:57:52.450 --> 00:57:53.617
Miss.

974
00:57:53.701 --> 00:57:55.624
Spaghetti aglio olio.

975
00:57:55.708 --> 00:57:57.042
I still remember.

976
00:57:58.180 --> 00:58:00.930
One spaghetti aglio olio,
one beef carbonara.

977
00:58:01.014 --> 00:58:02.472
[waitress] Okay. Please wait.

978
00:58:04.375 --> 00:58:05.964
Dad.

979
00:58:06.042 --> 00:58:08.875
- What?
- Have you heard from Bumi today?

980
00:58:13.531 --> 00:58:14.698
Actually, Kid...

981
00:58:14.904 --> 00:58:17.514
there's so much
I want to talk about with you.

982
00:58:17.753 --> 00:58:19.336
One of which is...

983
00:58:20.805 --> 00:58:23.305
I want us to be together again.

984
00:58:23.389 --> 00:58:24.764
Me...

985
00:58:24.847 --> 00:58:26.060
You...

986
00:58:26.125 --> 00:58:27.291
and your mother.

987
00:58:31.014 --> 00:58:32.305
Regarding Bumi...

988
00:58:34.542 --> 00:58:36.708
I want you to stay away from him.

989
00:58:36.781 --> 00:58:38.531
Why should I stay away from him?

990
00:58:39.538 --> 00:58:41.247
Dad.

991
00:58:41.331 --> 00:58:43.789
If it weren't for him,
I might have given up.

992
00:58:45.083 --> 00:58:46.833
I might have gone back to Paris.

993
00:58:46.920 --> 00:58:49.347
Forgetting the reason I came here.

994
00:58:49.430 --> 00:58:51.722
I also feel the same way.

995
00:58:51.805 --> 00:58:55.305
Bumi is kind, smart, handsome, polite,
just got a bachelor's degree.

996
00:58:55.389 --> 00:58:56.847
But nothing more than that.

997
00:58:56.930 --> 00:58:58.291
Why, Dad?

998
00:58:58.375 --> 00:59:00.167
Because he is not a good man for you.

999
00:59:05.818 --> 00:59:08.901
So, this is why
Bumi isn't picking up my calls?

1000
00:59:10.276 --> 00:59:12.859
One day your feelings can change, too.

1001
00:59:14.180 --> 00:59:15.305
I'm sure of it.

1002
00:59:18.312 --> 00:59:20.437
Can your feelings towards Mom change?

1003
00:59:23.375 --> 00:59:24.792
You're wrong!

1004
00:59:24.889 --> 00:59:27.055
[Paris] You're so wrong!

1005
00:59:27.139 --> 00:59:28.805
[Paris] Imagine.

1006
00:59:28.990 --> 00:59:30.791
When you choose a wife...

1007
00:59:30.875 --> 00:59:34.625
do you want your wife to remarry
when you die?

1008
00:59:35.805 --> 00:59:38.972
You never gave me a good example.

1009
00:59:39.042 --> 00:59:42.187
[Paris] How is that possible, Dad?
We have just met.

1010
00:59:42.271 --> 00:59:45.104
But you ask me to forget someone
who's already in my heart?

1011
00:59:46.347 --> 00:59:49.389
[Paris] Why are you so quick
to judge others?

1012
00:59:49.472 --> 00:59:53.555
Meanwhile, you needed that much time
to realize your own mistakes.

1013
00:59:55.216 --> 00:59:57.803
[Paris] It's enough
that you break Mom's heart.

1014
00:59:58.805 --> 01:00:01.428
Let me make my own choice, Dad.

1015
01:00:04.833 --> 01:00:06.732
Do you remember
why my name is Paris?

1016
01:00:09.542 --> 01:00:12.667
Because Mom only has me.

1017
01:00:12.765 --> 01:00:16.057
Mom can't have a man she loves.

1018
01:00:17.475 --> 01:00:19.597
Do you want that to happen to me too?

1019
01:00:19.680 --> 01:00:20.805
Paris.

1020
01:00:22.430 --> 01:00:23.597
[Sadewo] Sit down, Child.

1021
01:00:23.680 --> 01:00:24.889
[Sadewo] Sit down, darling.

1022
01:00:27.167 --> 01:00:28.667
Listen to me.

1023
01:00:28.748 --> 01:00:31.484
How could he teach me
if he didn't have experience?

1024
01:00:31.568 --> 01:00:36.014
I changed, I had a stance.
My life was changed because of him.

1025
01:00:36.097 --> 01:00:38.639
But I feel like
he's not the right man for you.

1026
01:00:38.833 --> 01:00:40.333
No.

1027
01:00:40.437 --> 01:00:41.521
No.

1028
01:00:42.514 --> 01:00:44.055
I hate you!

1029
01:00:44.139 --> 01:00:46.305
Forget him, Paris.

1030
01:00:46.389 --> 01:00:47.597
Paris.

1031
01:00:47.680 --> 01:00:55.680
[melodramatic music]

1032
01:00:57.139 --> 01:00:58.680
- [waitress] Please.
- Thank you.

1033
01:01:01.097 --> 01:01:09.097
[melodramatic music]

1034
01:01:13.014 --> 01:01:14.698
[Paris] What did you talk about
with my dad?

1035
01:01:14.722 --> 01:01:17.433
[music]

1036
01:01:17.514 --> 01:01:19.756
[Bumi] What your father said is true.

1037
01:01:21.722 --> 01:01:23.222
Bumi.

1038
01:01:23.491 --> 01:01:25.866
I don't agree
with my father deciding my soul mate.

1039
01:01:26.875 --> 01:01:29.875
[Paris] I was surprised
when Dad forbade us to meet again.

1040
01:01:29.976 --> 01:01:33.685
And what surprised me most,
why did you do what he asked?

1041
01:01:38.889 --> 01:01:41.849
You think I don't know
your history with your father?

1042
01:01:41.933 --> 01:01:44.475
And you think my being here
is a coincidence?

1043
01:01:46.796 --> 01:01:48.213
I'm waiting for you, Paris.

1044
01:01:50.764 --> 01:01:52.597
[Sadewo] Look there, kid. Look!

1045
01:01:52.678 --> 01:01:54.303
- Thank you, Ma'am.
- [Rahmi] Yes.

1046
01:01:54.389 --> 01:01:55.912
Thank you.

1047
01:01:57.292 --> 01:01:58.459
[Sadewo] Come on.

1048
01:02:01.238 --> 01:02:09.238
[splashing waves]

1049
01:02:15.958 --> 01:02:17.541
[little Paris] What is that?

1050
01:02:17.625 --> 01:02:19.297
This is my age.

1051
01:02:19.381 --> 01:02:20.499
Eight?

1052
01:02:20.583 --> 01:02:22.289
Today is my birthday.

1053
01:02:22.373 --> 01:02:24.124
Happy birthday.

1054
01:02:24.208 --> 01:02:25.416
[little Bumi] Thank you.

1055
01:02:29.555 --> 01:02:33.014
And I will always wait for you here
even though I'm not sure you'll come.

1056
01:02:33.097 --> 01:02:41.097
[melodramatic music]

1057
01:02:42.430 --> 01:02:43.805
I miss your stupid face.

1058
01:02:43.889 --> 01:02:51.349
[melodramatic music]

1059
01:02:51.430 --> 01:02:55.178
I'll never let go
what I should have.

1060
01:02:58.174 --> 01:02:59.632
And I always hoped...

1061
01:03:00.805 --> 01:03:04.889
I could take a photo with my father when
on my eighth birthday and the years after.

1062
01:03:04.972 --> 01:03:10.847
[melodramatic music]

1063
01:03:10.930 --> 01:03:13.472
And after meeting you,
I always hope again.

1064
01:03:16.097 --> 01:03:19.764
I don't want to lose you
even though your father will hinder me.

1065
01:03:19.847 --> 01:03:27.847
[melodramatic music]

1066
01:03:35.097 --> 01:03:38.198
[footsteps moving away]

1067
01:03:38.279 --> 01:03:45.430
[footsteps approaching]

1068
01:03:45.514 --> 01:03:47.139
Mom.

1069
01:03:51.458 --> 01:03:54.133
What's wrong?

1070
01:03:54.217 --> 01:03:55.717
[Bumi] Missing Dad, huh?

1071
01:03:59.250 --> 01:04:01.708
I once asked the police...

1072
01:04:01.792 --> 01:04:05.667
to track the suspected vehicle
that ran over your father...

1073
01:04:06.646 --> 01:04:09.229
based on on-site testimony.

1074
01:04:13.250 --> 01:04:14.875
But somehow...

1075
01:04:16.427 --> 01:04:18.343
the vehicle could not be tracked.

1076
01:04:23.180 --> 01:04:25.305
I'm only a commoner.

1077
01:04:27.443 --> 01:04:30.557
I didn't know what else I should do.

1078
01:04:30.757 --> 01:04:32.175
Calm down, Mom.

1079
01:04:39.783 --> 01:04:42.241
The person who took your father's life...

1080
01:04:44.014 --> 01:04:49.006
he also took away your life and my life.

1081
01:04:53.208 --> 01:04:56.125
He also killed any
chance for you to live...

1082
01:04:56.211 --> 01:04:58.461
with a father who loves you.

1083
01:04:59.753 --> 01:05:00.839
[sobbing]

1084
01:05:08.389 --> 01:05:09.930
[sobbing]

1085
01:05:10.146 --> 01:05:12.687
But that was a long time ago, Mom.

1086
01:05:14.125 --> 01:05:16.375
[Bumi] Are you still
looking for the perpetrator?

1087
01:05:16.461 --> 01:05:18.295
Do you want to sue the perpetrator?

1088
01:05:20.221 --> 01:05:21.929
If I sue, will...

1089
01:05:22.013 --> 01:05:23.804
your father come back?

1090
01:05:29.849 --> 01:05:30.849
Bumi.

1091
01:05:32.307 --> 01:05:36.390
Can you really forgive
the person who hit your father?

1092
01:05:48.635 --> 01:05:50.593
[Bumi] So, what do you want me to do, Mom?

1093
01:05:52.805 --> 01:05:54.014
Bumi.

1094
01:05:56.500 --> 01:05:59.755
Do you really like Paris?

1095
01:06:00.222 --> 01:06:02.305
What are you actually trying to say, Mom?

1096
01:06:02.500 --> 01:06:03.500
Wait.

1097
01:06:03.592 --> 01:06:05.430
Why are you suddenly asking that?

1098
01:06:05.514 --> 01:06:07.120
[chair scraping]

1099
01:06:20.339 --> 01:06:22.172
Are you willing to accept...

1100
01:06:23.000 --> 01:06:25.875
that the person who hit your father
was Paris' father?

1101
01:06:25.972 --> 01:06:32.068
[tense music]

1102
01:06:32.170 --> 01:06:40.170
[tense music]

1103
01:06:41.810 --> 01:06:43.639
Mom, where's Dad?

1104
01:06:43.722 --> 01:06:45.680
[Rahmi] Right, why hasn't he come home yet?

1105
01:06:46.722 --> 01:06:52.784
[walking back and forth]

1106
01:06:53.430 --> 01:06:54.680
Dad?

1107
01:06:58.037 --> 01:06:59.906
Ma'am, good evening.

1108
01:06:59.990 --> 01:07:03.094
We found your husband in an accident.

1109
01:07:03.178 --> 01:07:06.601
[Police officer] Because the distance is quite
far, we didn't see the perpetrator's face.

1110
01:07:06.625 --> 01:07:11.271
All we found was this note
and a cake, Ma'am.

1111
01:07:14.685 --> 01:07:15.764
[Police officer] Mom?

1112
01:07:15.847 --> 01:07:17.097
[Bumi] Mom!

1113
01:07:17.180 --> 01:07:18.347
[Bumi] Mom!

1114
01:07:19.430 --> 01:07:20.514
[Bumi] Mom!

1115
01:07:20.597 --> 01:07:23.448
- [Bumi] Mom!
- [Police officer] Ma'am?

1116
01:07:23.514 --> 01:07:25.612
[Police officer] Ma'am?

1117
