01:08:50.083 --> 01:08:58.083
[tense music]

1132
01:08:59.292 --> 01:09:00.874
[Peter] Oh, dear.

1133
01:09:00.958 --> 01:09:03.576
[Peter] Mr. Sadewo was very drunk.
I even had to carry him.

1134
01:09:03.660 --> 01:09:05.875
And what I remember was
Siska drove the car.

1135
01:09:05.958 --> 01:09:13.375
[melodramatic music]

1136
01:09:13.458 --> 01:09:20.875
[melodramatic music]

1137
01:09:20.958 --> 01:09:27.958
[melodramatic music]

1138
01:09:28.042 --> 01:09:33.749
[melodramatic music]

1139
01:09:33.833 --> 01:09:35.500
[Sadewo] You know what, kid?

1140
01:09:35.604 --> 01:09:38.187
[Sadewo] When your
mother took you to Paris...

1141
01:09:39.859 --> 01:09:41.526
I wasn't just broken.

1142
01:09:43.674 --> 01:09:45.091
I was numb.

1143
01:09:46.787 --> 01:09:49.412
Numb with devastation and loss.

1144
01:09:50.987 --> 01:09:52.154
I realized...

1145
01:09:53.351 --> 01:09:55.768
I couldn't throw away my broken heart.

1146
01:09:59.966 --> 01:10:03.216
But I have a piece of that broken heart
that I always keep.

1147
01:10:04.468 --> 01:10:06.218
The one that made me survive.

1148
01:10:14.300 --> 01:10:16.425
[Paris] What a funny analogy, Dad.

1149
01:10:19.085 --> 01:10:21.020
Is that why you break me?

1150
01:10:21.104 --> 01:10:22.187
[Sadewo] Wait.

1151
01:10:22.271 --> 01:10:23.687
[Sadewo] Why do you say that?

1152
01:10:24.667 --> 01:10:28.499
What I mean is every time I see Bumi,
it's as if I see a part of me.

1153
01:10:28.583 --> 01:10:29.708
That's it.

1154
01:10:29.804 --> 01:10:31.763
Bumi is not you!

1155
01:10:34.430 --> 01:10:36.222
And you should realize...

1156
01:10:36.305 --> 01:10:38.472
when you first met your child...

1157
01:10:38.555 --> 01:10:41.695
you should've made her happy.

1158
01:10:42.109 --> 01:10:43.616
Instead of bringing her down!

1159
01:10:43.700 --> 01:10:44.783
Listen, Paris.

1160
01:10:44.867 --> 01:10:47.249
Humans need to learn to fall
to learn to get up.

1161
01:10:47.333 --> 01:10:49.750
It takes a sense of loss
to be able to learn to find.

1162
01:10:50.292 --> 01:10:53.208
And it needs free space
to be able to grow and develop.

1163
01:10:53.305 --> 01:10:55.139
I've lost everything.

1164
01:10:55.222 --> 01:10:56.430
I've experienced that.

1165
01:10:58.070 --> 01:11:01.347
I don't want you to lose yourself.

1166
01:11:01.430 --> 01:11:04.389
[melodramatic music]

1167
01:11:04.472 --> 01:11:05.639
You know what, Paris?

1168
01:11:06.972 --> 01:11:11.180
For every man, there is only one woman
in his heart all his life.

1169
01:11:11.264 --> 01:11:14.222
It doesn't matter
whether he'll get her or not.

1170
01:11:14.292 --> 01:11:21.208
[melodramatic music]

1171
01:11:21.273 --> 01:11:23.430
Do you know what I'm doing?

1172
01:11:23.514 --> 01:11:26.805
[melodramatic music]

1173
01:11:26.889 --> 01:11:28.055
Dad...

1174
01:11:29.518 --> 01:11:32.976
I'm fighting for what I truly love...

1175
01:11:36.389 --> 01:11:38.264
instead of giving up.

1176
01:11:38.347 --> 01:11:42.014
Because I don't know
what else I want to fight for.

1177
01:11:42.097 --> 01:11:44.847
I'm not you. Bumi is not you.

1178
01:11:44.930 --> 01:11:46.290
- [Sadewo] Calm down.
- [Paris] No!

1179
01:11:48.750 --> 01:11:50.062
[Sadewo] Don't cry.

1180
01:11:52.203 --> 01:11:53.439
[door knocking]

1181
01:11:53.514 --> 01:11:55.892
[sobbing]

1182
01:11:57.680 --> 01:12:00.205
[running footsteps]

1183
01:12:01.415 --> 01:12:07.939
[sobbing]

1184
01:12:08.042 --> 01:12:15.458
[melodramatic music]

1185
01:12:15.542 --> 01:12:22.958
[melodramatic music]

1186
01:12:23.042 --> 01:12:29.775
[melodramatic music]

1187
01:12:29.859 --> 01:12:31.401
You haven't changed much.

1188
01:12:33.389 --> 01:12:36.139
Nobody changes.

1189
01:12:36.223 --> 01:12:37.931
I will change...

1190
01:12:38.015 --> 01:12:40.224
if you give me one more chance.

1191
01:12:44.847 --> 01:12:47.472
But I have to take responsibility
for something.

1192
01:12:49.143 --> 01:12:52.768
I might not be able to revive
the father of a child.

1193
01:12:55.097 --> 01:12:56.514
But at least...

1194
01:12:58.265 --> 01:13:00.265
I can give him justice.

1195
01:13:01.722 --> 01:13:03.097
Are you sure?

1196
01:13:04.365 --> 01:13:06.028
Are you...

1197
01:13:06.389 --> 01:13:08.264
doing this...

1198
01:13:08.347 --> 01:13:12.330
just because he's the man
your daughter loves?

1199
01:13:13.375 --> 01:13:14.667
No, Aryana.

1200
01:13:17.554 --> 01:13:21.263
I'm doing it because I want
to do something right in my life.

1201
01:13:22.620 --> 01:13:23.787
I'm tired.

1202
01:13:25.242 --> 01:13:29.451
Tired because all my life,
I have to make amends for all my mistakes.

1203
01:13:36.639 --> 01:13:39.180
I want us to be together again.

1204
01:13:42.180 --> 01:13:43.930
Me...

1205
01:13:44.014 --> 01:13:45.222
Paris...

1206
01:13:46.222 --> 01:13:47.389
and you.

1207
01:13:49.099 --> 01:13:52.766
[melodramatic music]

1208
01:13:52.847 --> 01:13:54.139
[Sadewo] Forgive me.

1209
01:13:54.222 --> 01:14:02.222
[melodramatic music]

1210
01:14:05.722 --> 01:14:07.264
[Sadewo] Will you forgive me?

